# OS / base-image CVEs (zlib, libpng) from nginx:alpine. Re-evaluate after `apk upgrade` + image rebuild each release.
# This image only serves static HTML/JS/CSS; nginx does not run zlib untgz; libpng decode paths are unused for typical SPA hosting.
# Remove entries when `docker build` + Trivy show clean, or when Alpine packages ship fixed versions.
#
# GitHub Security alert mapping (Trivy / container scan):
#   #2 libpng use-after-free -> CVE-2026-25646
#   #3 libpng Neon palette OOB -> CVE-2026-33416, CVE-2026-33636
#   #4 zlib untgz buffer overflow -> CVE-2026-22184
#   #5 zlib CRC32 infinite loop -> CVE-2026-27171

# libpng - heap buffer overflow in png_set_quantize
CVE-2026-25646 exp:2026-06-01T00:00:00Z

# libpng - use-after-free (png_set_tRNS / png_set_PLTE); Neon palette expansion (ARM)
CVE-2026-33416 exp:2026-06-01T00:00:00Z
CVE-2026-33636 exp:2026-06-01T00:00:00Z

# zlib - untgz utility overflow (CVE-2026-22184: affects contrib/untgz, not nginx gzip static serving)
# zlib - CRC32 combine infinite loop (CVE-2026-27171)
CVE-2026-22184 exp:2026-06-01T00:00:00Z
